[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Romance of the Three Kingdoms II
	]em
	" is the second in the 
	[em 
		"Romance of the Three Kingdoms
	]em
	" series of turn-based strategy games produced by Koei and based on a historical novel. Players choose from one of six scenarios that determine the initial layout of power in ancient China. The scenarios loosely depict allegiances and territories controlled by the warlords as according to the novel, although gameplay does not follow events in the novel after the game begins.
]div
